# TASK_PACKET

Task ID
CRUSHR-BENCH-01

Title
Plumb canonical benchmark harness, schemas, and live-corpus evaluation mode

Role
BUILDER

Objective
Implement the benchmark harness specified in the benchmark harness spec bundle, wire in the raw-record and summary schemas, and add a bounded live-corpus evaluation mode so crushr can produce both publishable canonical benchmark evidence and exploratory real-world results.

This packet exists because crushr now needs quantitative evidence rather than qualitative architectural claims.

The goal is to make it possible to:
1. run deterministic benchmark suites that generate whitepaper-quality metrics
2. run the same measurement pipeline against real downloaded corpora for exploratory evaluation
3. emit machine-readable raw records and summaries suitable for charts, tables, and later documentation integration

This is a plumbing + evidence packet.
It is not a format-redesign packet.

