Acceptance criteria

This packet is acceptable only if all of the following are true:

1. Benchmark manifest ingestion works.
2. Raw per-scenario records are emitted in schema-conforming form.
3. Grouped summary output is emitted in schema-conforming form.
4. Benchmark CLI commands exist and are runnable.
5. Live corpus mode exists and is clearly labeled exploratory.
6. Required quantitative metrics are present.
7. Correctness invariant metrics are explicit and visible.
8. At least one canonical benchmark run and one live-corpus run have been executed successfully and included in the submission.
9. The resulting outputs are sufficient to start building real evidence tables and charts for the whitepaper.

